      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "RHYTHMIC ENERGY (5) charged out of the boxes with a fast early split and led throughout to score when a one length winner (25.28) over 450m at Ballarat. Winner at his latest appearance in one of the quickest times on the card. Can make it two on the bounce. PAW LAMPADES (7) hit the ground running last time with a fast early split and never headed, leading throughout to win by 5 lengths (23.18) over 410m at this track. Yet to win out of this box but has been in the placings two times from four starts. Can make it back-to-back wins. PAW NIMBUS (4) had some strong recent form but was below best last time when sixth (29.91) in a Grade 4 at Sandown. Drifted back and never in it from the wide draw. Has won two of three starts from this draw. Has ability and is one of the better chances. WITCH OF NOVA (1) hit the frame latest (22.61) when third at Shepparton in a Grade 5. Has two wins already from this draw.",
